of Moths, no nor the fret of Time, which the beſt of worldly things are ſubjected to, and by which come not only not to be; but while they are, to be as if they were not: Of which that of the Epigrammatiſt is true;
Fundus Achamenidae fueram, nunc cedo Menippo;
Mox alium rurſus, mox aliúmque ſequar;
