But (O holy ſoul) all is not Gold that gliſters, all ſufferings are not ſanctified to ſufferers, becauſe Pride and Folly has Martyrs which Chriſt crowns not, Chriſts ſlock hear his voice, and not a ſtrangers;

keep in the fold, not wander into by-wayes; Let it be thy care to ſuffer not as a buſie body, not as an enemy to Government, and a ſubverter of Order and civil Peace;

                        Non erga qui propter iniquitatem, et propter Chriſtianae unitatis impiam diviſionem; ſed qui propter juſtitiam perſecutionem patiuntur, 
